>> source: https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/mexican-penne-avocado
>> time required: 30 minutes
>> image: https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/mexican-penne-5cd4efb.jpg?resize=768,574

Cook the pasta @in{196%g} salted water for ~{10-12%min}s until al dente. Meanwhile, heat the @oil{1%tsp} in a medium pan. Add the sliced @onion{1%large} and @pepper{1} and fry, stirring frequently for ~{10%min}s until golden. Stir in the @garlic{2%clove} and spices, then tip in the @tomatoes{400%g}, half a can of water, the corn and @bouillon{1%tsp}. Cover and simmer for ~{15%min}s.

Meanwhile, toss the @avocado{1} with the @lime{0.5} juice and zest, and the finely chopped onion.

Drain the @penne{100%g} and toss into the sauce with the @coriander{1%tsp}. Spoon the pasta into bowls, top with the avocado and scatter over the @coriander{0%handful} leaves.
